&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DevOps Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Calgary, AB (Hybrid – 3 days/week in our beautiful downtown office)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re looking for a highly skilled &lt;strong&gt;Senior DevOps Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our dynamic team and help shape the future of our infrastructure and delivery pipelines. This is an opportunity to work on cutting-edge technologies, collaborate with talented professionals, and make a real impact on the scalability and reliability of our products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architect and Build:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and implement scalable, modular solutions that integrate seamlessly across our diverse product suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate and Innovate:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with cross-functional teams to understand requirements and incorporate user feedback into robust solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Best Practices:&lt;/strong&gt; Champion modern software architecture principles, including &lt;strong&gt;Microservices&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Serverless computing&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;API-first strategies&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Containerization:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and execute strategies for containerization and orchestration using &lt;strong&gt;Docker&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Kubernetes&lt;/strong&gt;, or similar technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensure Reliability:&lt;/strong&gt; Maintain a secure, compliant, and resilient infrastructure aligned with industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mentor and Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as an escalation point for L1 operations, troubleshoot complex issues, and provide training on product-specific domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead product and infrastructure enhancements identified through blameless postmortems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weekend Rotation:&lt;/strong&gt; Participate in scheduled weekend support rotations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 3–5 years in &lt;strong&gt;Site Reliability Engineering&lt;/strong&gt; or similar roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on coding experience with &lt;strong&gt;Go&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Python&lt;/strong&gt;, and/or &lt;strong&gt;Shell scripting&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in &lt;strong&gt;cloud platforms&lt;/strong&gt; (AWS, GCP, Azure) and &lt;strong&gt;container technologies&lt;/strong&gt; (Docker, Kubernetes).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in &lt;strong&gt;CI/CD pipelines&lt;/strong&gt; and modern delivery ecosystems (GitHub Actions, ArgoCD, Harness.io, GitLab CI, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
